[normal]Audience figures[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The growth
[normal] in the global audience figure
[normal] this year
[normal] was outstanding, with overall Global News
[normal] 
[normal]reaching
[normal] 
[normal]256m
[normal] people
[normal] -
[normal] 17m 
[normal](7% increase) 
[normal]more than last year and exceeding the target for 2013 of 245m by a significant margin. 
[normal]Taking into account audiences for BBC World Service, BBC World News and the website 
[normal]bbc.com/news
[normal], around the world, one in every 28 people is a viewer, listener or reader of BBC global news.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The increase was primarily driven by a growth of 8m in digital audiences and 13m uplift in World Service TV audi
[normal]ences. The online growth is particularly impressive, growing 26% from a flat position last year. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]BBC 
[normal]WS audiences were up to 192m
[normal].  
[normal]A
[normal]udiences to BBC Arabic
[normal] across platforms
[normal] went up to 33m, an increase of 7m, suggesting that audiences gained during the Ar
[normal]ab Uprising continue to turn to the BBC for trusted news.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]W[bold]orld [bold]S[bold]ervice[bold] TV:[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]World Service digital:[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The BBC’s global TV and digital operations, BBC World News and bbc.com/news, were brought together to form 
[normal]t
[normal]he new business entity GN
[normal] Ltd
[normal].
[normal] in order to drive bigger audiences
[normal] and greater multimedia working
[normal]. 
[normal] 
[normal]GN Ltd. 
[normal]serves a glo
[normal]bal audience of over 88 million with 
[normal]major growth in bbc.com/news audiences.
[normal] The website reached one billion page views in August - a major milestone.
[normal]Th
[normal]e
[normal] marked 
[normal]increase in the BBC Global News audience illustrates that there is a growing worldwide audience for impartial, trustworthy journalism.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] The World Service is emerging from a very difficult period of funding cuts and the closure of services
[normal] including most re
[normal]cently the 
[normal]cessation of Arabic short wave across the Middle East (except to Sudan), and the reduction of Arabic and English medium wave hours to the Middle East
[normal], but audiences have increased despite this, thanks to the quality of its journalism, and decisi
[normal]ons taken to invest in new offers such as TV and online in order to remain relevant to audiences in the growing international media market.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Trust and [bold]q[bold]uality measurements[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]A new assessment of the global BBC brand shows that 
[normal]the BBC is ahead of all 
[normal]competitors on all attributes globally, and most closely associated with trust, high quality
[normal] [bold]and being unbiased and objective. 
[normal] Where the BBC was less strong – on engagement – efforts have been made to increase regular usage and loyalty amongst the global 
[normal]audience.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The ‘Brand Tracker’ was
[normal] established this year to monitor the international brand position of Global News. 
[normal] 
[normal]Research 
[normal]was
[normal] conducted in ten markets, and 
[normal]r
[normal]esults so far show that the BBC and CNN are clear leaders with the BBC slightly ahead, with bo
[normal]th gaining significantly higher levels of awareness and consideration than the competition. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Performance varies considerably by market, w
[normal]hilst
[normal] CNN 
[normal]i
[normal]s 
[normal]the BBC’s
[normal] closest competitor globally, both Al Jazeera English and Euronews having a strong presence in t
[normal]heir respective primary markets. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In terms of brand attributes, the BBC is ahead of all competitors on all attributes globally, and most closely associated with trust, high quality
[normal] [bold]and being unbiased and objective. There are also indications that the BBC 
[normal]gains greater social currency and impact
[normal] [bold]from its coverage than key competitors. However, 
[normal]the tracker showed that 
[normal]the BBC 
[normal]was 
[normal]not as strong
[normal] on 
[normal]attributes such as 
[normal]being passionate
[normal] 
[normal]and
[normal] dynamic
[normal] 
[normal]– 
[normal]this is being addressed through 
[normal]‘Live the Story’, the World New
[normal]s, World Service and bbc.com/news 
[normal]marketing campaign 
[normal]launched to improve the brand image of global news output.  The campaign emphasises that bringing stories to life in an engaging fashion is a key editorial priority for Global News, and new tools and gui
[normal]delines 
[normal]to facilitate this 
[normal]were made available 
[normal]to staff 
[normal]across the division.
